---
import PageLayout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '~/components/directory/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import config from '~/config';

const title = 'Terms of Service';
const description = `Terms of Service for ${config.brandName}. Review the terms governing use of the ${config.domain} directory, quote requests, provider listings, and related services.`;
const metadata = { title, description };
const currentYear = new Date().getFullYear();
const effectiveDate = 'March 23, 2026';
---
<PageLayout metadata={metadata}>
  <Fragment slot="announcement"><span></span></Fragment>
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8">
    <Breadcrumbs crumbs={[{ label: 'Terms of Service' }]} />

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-default mb-6">Terms of Service</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <p class="text-sm text-muted">Effective Date: {effectiveDate} &mdash; Last Updated: {effectiveDate}</p>

      <p>
        These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your access to and use of the website located at
        <a href={`https://${config.domain}`}>{config.domain}</a> (the "Site"), operated by {config.brandName}
        ("we," "us," or "our"). By accessing or using the Site, you agree to be bound by these Terms. If you
        do not agree to these Terms, you must not use the Site.
      </p>
      <p>
        These Terms apply to all visitors, attorneys, legal professionals, {config.primaryKeyword}s, and any
        other users of the Site (collectively, "you" or "users"). We may update these Terms from time to time;
        the "Last Updated" date above reflects the most recent revision. Continued use of the Site after any
        changes constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Description of Service</h2>
      <p>
        {config.brandName} is an online directory that helps attorneys and litigation teams locate and evaluate
        {config.primaryKeyword}s across the United States. The Site aggregates publicly available business
        information, allows service providers to claim and manage their listings, and enables visitors to submit
        quote requests directly to listed providers.
      </p>
      <p>
        We do not employ, endorse, or guarantee any {config.primaryKeyword} listed on the Site. We are not a
        party to any agreement between you and a service provider, and we do not participate in the actual
        delivery of {config.servicePhrase} or any related professional services.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Acceptable Use</h2>
      <p>You agree to use the Site only for lawful purposes and in accordance with these Terms. Specifically, you agree not to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use the Site to transmit any material that is unlawful, threatening, abusive, defamatory, invasive of privacy, or otherwise objectionable</li>
        <li>Submit false, misleading, or fraudulent information through quote request forms, listing claims, or any other Site feature</li>
        <li>Impersonate any person or entity, or falsely represent your affiliation with any person or entity</li>
        <li>Use automated scripts, bots, scrapers, or other automated means to access the Site or extract data from it without our prior written consent</li>
        <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any portion of the Site, its servers, or any systems or networks connected to the Site</li>
        <li>Interfere with or disrupt the operation of the Site or the servers or networks used to make the Site available</li>
        <li>Use information obtained from the Site to harass, solicit, or send unsolicited communications to any listed provider</li>
        <li>Reproduce, duplicate, copy, sell, resell, or otherwise exploit any portion of the Site for commercial purposes without our express written permission</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We reserve the right to suspend or terminate your access to the Site, without notice, if we reasonably
        believe you have violated these Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Quote Requests</h2>
      <p>
        The Site allows visitors to submit quote requests to one or more listed {config.primaryKeyword}s.
        When you submit a quote request, you provide information including your name, contact details, case
        description, and scheduling preferences. This information is forwarded directly to the provider(s)
        you select.
      </p>
      <p>By submitting a quote request, you acknowledge and agree that:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>You are providing your information voluntarily and understand it will be shared with the selected provider(s)</li>
        <li>We do not guarantee that any provider will respond to your request, or that any response will meet your needs</li>
        <li>Once your information is transmitted to a provider, that provider's handling of your information is governed by their own privacy practices, not ours</li>
        <li>Submission of a quote request does not create a contract, engagement, or obligation between you and any provider or between you and {config.brandName}</li>
        <li>You will not submit quote requests for frivolous, fraudulent, or non-genuine purposes</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        For details on how we handle quote request data, please review our <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Provider Listings</h2>

      <h3>a. Publicly Sourced Listings</h3>
      <p>
        {config.brandName} compiles business listing information from publicly available sources including Google Maps,
        professional registries, licensing boards, trade associations, review platforms, and publicly accessible
        business websites. We organize and present this information to help users find qualified
        {config.primaryKeyword}s.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you are a business owner or authorized representative and wish to correct or remove a listing sourced
        from public data, please contact us at <a href={`mailto:${config.contactEmail}`}>{config.contactEmail}</a>.
        We will process corrections within 5 business days and removal requests within 5 business days.
      </p>

      <h3>b. Claimed and Managed Listings</h3>
      <p>
        Service providers may claim their listings to manage business information, add photographs, update service
        descriptions, and respond to quote requests. By claiming a listing, you represent and warrant that:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>You are the owner of the business or an authorized representative with authority to manage the listing</li>
        <li>All information you provide is accurate, current, and complete</li>
        <li>You will promptly update your listing if any information becomes inaccurate or outdated</li>
        <li>You hold all necessary licenses, certifications, and permits required to provide the services described in your listing</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>c. Paid Listing Tiers</h3>
      <p>
        {config.brandName} offers paid listing tiers that provide enhanced visibility and additional features for
        service providers. Paid listing tiers may include benefits such as priority placement, enhanced profile
        features, and additional analytics. Paid status does not affect editorial content, review ratings, or
        the substance of any listing information.
      </p>
      <p>
        Payment terms, tier features, and pricing are described on our <a href="/pricing/">Pricing</a> page.
        All fees are non-refundable unless otherwise stated in writing. We reserve the right to modify pricing
        and tier features upon 30 days' written notice to affected providers.
      </p>

      <h3>d. Listing Removal and Suspension</h3>
      <p>
        We reserve the right to remove, suspend, or modify any listing at our sole discretion, including but not
        limited to listings that contain inaccurate information, violate these Terms, or are the subject of
        credible complaints from users or other providers. We will make reasonable efforts to notify the affected
        provider before taking action, except where immediate action is necessary to protect users or the integrity
        of the directory.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Content Ownership and Intellectual Property</h2>

      <h3>a. Our Content</h3>
      <p>
        The Site and its original content (including but not limited to text, graphics, logos, page layouts, city
        guides, blog articles, and editorial content) are the property of {config.brandName} and are protected by
        United States copyright, trademark, and other intellectual property laws. You may not reproduce, distribute,
        modify, create derivative works of, publicly display, or otherwise exploit our content without our prior
        written consent.
      </p>

      <h3>b. Third-Party Content</h3>
      <p>
        The Site incorporates data from third-party sources including map data from OpenStreetMap (used under the
        <a href="https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open Data Commons Open Database License</a>),
        review data from public platforms, and business information from public records. Such content remains
        subject to the terms and licenses of its respective sources.
      </p>

      <h2>6. User Submissions</h2>
      <p>
        By submitting any content to the Site &mdash; including but not limited to quote request details, listing
        information, photographs, business descriptions, and any other materials ("User Submissions") &mdash; you
        grant {config.brandName} a non-exclusive, royalty-free, worldwide, perpetual license to use, reproduce, modify,
        adapt, publish, and display such User Submissions in connection with operating and improving the Site.
      </p>
      <p>You represent and warrant that:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>You own or have the necessary rights to submit the content</li>
        <li>Your submissions do not infringe the intellectual property rights, privacy rights, or any other rights of any third party</li>
        <li>Your submissions do not contain any material that is unlawful, defamatory, or otherwise objectionable</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We reserve the right to remove any User Submission that, in our sole judgment, violates these Terms or is
        otherwise objectionable. We are not obligated to monitor, review, or edit User Submissions, but we may do so
        at our discretion.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Disclaimers</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>The Site is provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis, without warranties of any kind, either
        express or implied.</strong> To the fullest extent permitted by applicable law, {config.brandName} disclaims all
        warranties, including but not limited to implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular
        purpose, and non-infringement.
      </p>
      <p>Without limiting the foregoing, we do not warrant that:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>The Site will be available without interruption or error</li>
        <li>Any information on the Site (including listing data, reviews, ratings, certifications, or business details) is accurate, complete, current, or reliable</li>
        <li>Any {config.primaryKeyword} listed on the Site is licensed, insured, qualified, or competent to perform the services described</li>
        <li>The results of any quote request or provider engagement will be satisfactory</li>
        <li>The Site is free of viruses, malware, or other harmful components</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        You acknowledge that you use the Site and rely on its content at your own risk. You are solely responsible
        for conducting your own due diligence before engaging any service provider, including verifying credentials,
        insurance, references, and suitability for your particular matter.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, {config.brandName}, its owners, officers, employees,
        agents, and affiliates shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive
        damages arising out of or related to your use of or inability to use the Site.</strong> This includes, without
        limitation, damages for lost profits, lost data, loss of goodwill, business interruption, or any other
        intangible losses, even if we have been advised of the possibility of such damages.
      </p>
      <p>
        Without limiting the foregoing, our total aggregate liability to you for all claims arising out of or related
        to the Site or these Terms shall not exceed the greater of (a) the amount you have paid to {config.brandName} in
        the twelve (12) months preceding the event giving rise to the claim, or (b) one hundred dollars ($100.00).
      </p>
      <p>
        This limitation of liability applies to all claims, whether based on warranty, contract, tort (including
        negligence), strict liability, or any other legal theory, and whether or not we have been informed of the
        possibility of such damage.
      </p>
      <p>
        {config.brandName} is not liable for any act or omission of any {config.primaryKeyword} listed on the Site,
        including but not limited to the quality of their work product, their failure to appear at a scheduled
        engagement, equipment malfunctions, breaches of confidentiality, or any other aspect of their performance.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Indemnification</h2>
      <p>
        You agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless {config.brandName}, its owners, officers, employees, agents,
        and affiliates from and against any and all claims, liabilities, damages, losses, costs, and expenses
        (including reasonable attorneys' fees) arising out of or related to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your use of the Site</li>
        <li>Your violation of these Terms</li>
        <li>Your violation of any rights of any third party</li>
        <li>Any User Submission you provide</li>
        <li>Any dispute between you and a service provider contacted through the Site</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>10. Dispute Resolution</h2>

      <h3>a. Informal Resolution</h3>
      <p>
        Before initiating any formal dispute resolution proceeding, you agree to first contact us at
        <a href={`mailto:${config.contactEmail}`}>{config.contactEmail}</a> and attempt to resolve the dispute
        informally. We will make good-faith efforts to resolve any concern or dispute within 30 days of receipt.
      </p>

      <h3>b. Governing Law</h3>
      <p>
        These Terms and any disputes arising out of or related to these Terms or the Site shall be governed by
        and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of Texas, without regard to its conflict of law
        provisions.
      </p>

      <h3>c. Jurisdiction and Venue</h3>
      <p>
        Any legal action or proceeding arising out of or related to these Terms or the Site shall be brought
        exclusively in the state or federal courts located in Travis County, Texas. You consent to the personal
        jurisdiction and venue of such courts and waive any objection based on inconvenient forum.
      </p>

      <h3>d. Limitation on Claims</h3>
      <p>
        Any cause of action or claim you may have arising out of or related to these Terms or the Site must be
        commenced within one (1) year after the cause of action accrues. Otherwise, such cause of action or claim
        is permanently barred.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Third-Party Links</h2>
      <p>
        The Site may contain links to third-party websites, including provider websites, review platforms, and
        external resources. These links are provided for your convenience only. We do not control, endorse, or
        assume any responsibility for the content, privacy policies, or practices of any third-party website.
        Your interactions with any third-party website are solely between you and that third party.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Severability</h2>
      <p>
        If any provision of these Terms is held to be invalid, illegal, or unenforceable by a court of competent
        jurisdiction, the remaining provisions shall continue in full force and effect. The invalid or unenforceable
        provision shall be modified to the minimum extent necessary to make it valid and enforceable while preserving
        its original intent.
      </p>

      <h2>13. Entire Agreement</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms, together with our <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a> and any applicable listing agreements,
        constitute the entire agreement between you and {config.brandName} regarding your use of the Site. These Terms
        supersede all prior or contemporaneous communications, proposals, and agreements, whether oral or written,
        between you and {config.brandName} with respect to the Site.
      </p>

      <h2>14. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>If you have questions about these Terms of Service, you may contact us at:</p>
      <address class="not-italic">
        <strong>{config.brandName}</strong><br />
        PO Box 1547<br />
        Austin, TX 78767<br /><br />
        Email: <a href={`mailto:${config.contactEmail}`}>{config.contactEmail}</a><br />
        Website: <a href={`https://${config.domain}`}>{config.domain}</a>
      </address>

      <p class="text-sm text-muted mt-8">
        &copy; {currentYear} {config.brandName}. All rights reserved.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
